[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_jim46")
reagent_id = "NH4NO3"
title = "Ammonium nitrate"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]NH₄NO₃[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]80 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]White solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
NH₃ + HNO₃ → NH₄NO₃
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound made of ammonium (NH₄⁺) and nitrate (NO₃⁻) ions.  
• Highly soluble in water.  
• Strong oxidizing compound.
[b]Where ammonium nitrate is found[/b]
• Produced in the chemical industry.  
• Used widely in agriculture.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Fertilizers.  
• Used in cold packs because dissolving absorbs heat.  
• Used in some industrial explosives.
[b]Safety[/b]
Can decompose explosively under high heat or contamination.  
Must be stored and handled carefully."
